            </article>
            <article class="outcome-item">
              <strong>2. The tracker becomes the source of truth</strong>
              <p>Each row carries expected behavior, acceptance checks, test status, errors, fix status, retest result, and evidence.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="outcome-item">
              <strong>3. The final answer is audit-ready</strong>
              <p>You get what passed, what failed, what was fixed, what needs approval, and what remains risky.</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
